    en: "A certified copy of a marriage certificate is the official proof of marriage. New York issues copies through the city, town, or village clerk where the marriage license was originally issued, or through NY State Vital Records. NY Domestic Relations Law § 14-a controls who can request a copy. Couples typically need certified copies for name changes, immigration filings, passport applications, divorce paperwork, real estate transactions, and survivor benefit claims. Cost varies by issuing office — local clerks usually charge $10 to $20 per copy, NY State Vital Records charges $30."
